Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name, Timarchidas. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0026.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0975)
